        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2025-03-14T19:55:23Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Making Advancements in Commercial Hypersonics Act or the MACH Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill permits the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) to establish a research program to facilitate the testing of high-speed aircraft and related technologies, to be known as the Making Advancements in Commercial Hypersonics Program.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Within a specified time period, NASA must develop a strategic plan for such research. NASA must also consult with the Department of Defense and the Federal Aviation Administration on these efforts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Under the program, NASA may not (1) fund the development of hypersonic and related technologies; or (2) enter into an agreement with certain foreign entities of concern, including entities owned or controlled by China, Iran, North Korea, or Russia.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
